news.title: Vietnam's No Va Land to hold board meeting amid creditor pressure
news.para: The property developer was urged in September to negotiate a debt restructuring agreement by a group of international creditors with combined 75% ownership of the 2026 unsecured convertible bond.

news.title: China's Country Garden default on dollar bond declared for first time
news.para: Country Garden’s failure to pay interest on the note within a grace period that ended last week “constitutes an event of default,” according to a notice to holders from trustee Citicorp International Ltd seen by Bloomberg News.

news.title: NGT asks Haryana to give list of stone crushers in two districts
news.para: According to a report submitted by the Haryana government to NGT last month, out of the 133 units operating in Mahendergarh, 49 were found to be violating the provisions of a 2016 notification on stone crushers as well as those of the Air (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1981.

news.title: Bombay HC lets tenants get nod to reconstruct razed building themselves
news.para: The building on Aarey Road, Goregaon West, was constructed in 1965, and the BMC declared it dangerous in 2014. The building was vacated in July 2019 and demolished.

news.title: Ludhiana: Proposed conversion of residential area into commercial slammed
news.para: The MLA made the recommendation after owners of the commercial properties approached him. However, residents of adjoining streets and lanes fear that it will damage the original plan of the area.

news.title: Mumbai air pollution: City turns a giant construction site, is adding five Nariman Points
news.para: The construction frenzy—one of the factors responsible for appalling air pollution—is the result of a major sop given by the state government to builders during the Covid lockdown in 2021: slashing premiums by half. In turn, the BMC earned a record Rs 15,000 crore from developers that year.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Over 1,600 GDA housing units up for grabs
news.para: Total 1,629 units across eight housing schemes, including Madhuban Bapudham, are up for grabs. The per unit cost ranges between Rs 5.7 lakh for EWS units and Rs 69.42 lakh for 3BHKs.

news.title: Metro cess on property registrations in four Maharashtra cities hits Rs 3,600 crore
news.para: It is collected through stamp duty registration of documents for sale, gift and mortgage of properties. In Mumbai, the duty was raised from 5% to 6%, and in the other cities, it was raised from 6% to 7%.

news.title: Gurugram: Checks at building sites to curb dust rule violations
news.para: The development came after rising air pollution from construction sites and developers and property owners not adhering to rules under stage 2 of GRAP.

news.title: Piramal Group gets premium for Rs 531 crore residual bad loans
news.para: These loans have been sold to Omkara Asset Reconstruction Co., giving Omkara full ownership of all loans linked to this exposure. These loans, reflected as receivables in the form of security receipts (SR) on Piramal's books, are now being sold for upfront cash.

news.title: Macrotech Developers raises Rs 650-crore to refinance high-cost debt
news.para: Standard Chartered Bank provided Rs 245 crore at 9% payable annually, while Deutsche Bank provided Rs 405 crore at 9.5% payable quarterly, the people said.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Precision Realty Developers
news.para: In February 2017, L&T Finance had sanctioned a loan of Rs 200 crore in favour of the original borrowing entity Kaa Vee Retail Infra, which was later merged with Precision Realty Developers.

news.title: China government's land sales revenue drops in September 2023
news.para: Land sales revenues in September fell 21.3% from a year earlier, after falling 22.2% the previous month, according to Reuters calculations based on the ministry's data.

news.title: Vadodara: Shops without fire safety face heat
news.para: On Monday, four commercial complexes including the Sitaram Complex and Kunj Plaza in Chhani, VIP View Complex in Karelibaug as well as Maruti Complex in Nizampura were sealed.

news.title: Noida: Air turns 'very poor', but demolition waste dumping goes unchecked here
news.para: Though the Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) implemented stage 2 of the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) in DelhiNCR and adjoining areas on Saturday, the same is not visible on the ground.

news.title: MCD issues 24 challans for dumping of C&D waste in Delhi
news.para: MCD has formed 511 surveillance teams, comprising 1,064 officials, to check open burning, illegal construction, demolition waste dumping and dust on roads. It has also stationed 35 anti-smog guns at high rise buildings and landfills.

news.title: Nashik civic body sends notices to 2.4 lakh property tax defaulters
news.para: The NMC has directed the defaulters to clear their tax dues within 15 days, failing which, the civic body will start the process of issuing warrants.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government hikes payout for phase-2 of Noida airport by Rs 880 crore
news.para: Officials said 70% of acquisition of 1,181 hectares of land across six villages in Jewar — Ranhera, Kureb, Karauli Bangar, Dayanatpur, Beerampur and Mudharah — has been completed and compensation of Rs 2,800 crore distributed to farmers till now.

news.title: Density a pivotal issue: Chief architect on Chandigarh master plan
news.para: Surinder Bahga, a city-based architect, pointed out lack of a proper documentation process to identify heritage buildings, uncertainties over preservation methods and responsible parties, and the need for a clear administrative approach.

news.title: Daily property registrations in Maharashtra witness uptick in past week
news.para: This was the trend in September too, a registration official said on Monday. Data showed that from October 16, the registrations were over 11,000 a day and October 20 witnessed the highest daily log (13,569) for the month.
